8. Optional: Auto-Update Setting

Add a setting to control update behavior:

```javascript
// Add to localStorage management
const updateSettings = {
    autoCheck: true,
    autoInstall: false, // Set to true for automatic updates
    lastVersion: APP_VERSION
};

// Save settings
function saveUpdateSettings(settings) {
    localStorage.setItem('updateSettings', JSON.stringify(settings));
}

// Load settings
function loadUpdateSettings() {
    const saved = localStorage.getItem('updateSettings');
    if (saved) {
        Object.assign(updateSettings, JSON.parse(saved));
    }
    return updateSettings;
}
```

How It Works:

1. Check for Updates: The app periodically checks version.json on your server
2. Notify User: When a new version is found, shows a modal with release notes
3. Update Process: User clicks "Update Now" which:
   · Updates the service worker
   · Waits for activation
   · Reloads the page with new version
4. Smart Notifications: Won't repeatedly notify about the same version
5. Offline Support: Works within the PWA offline-first architecture

Deployment Notes:

1. Upload version.json to your web server with the current version number
2. Increment APP_VERSION in app.js and CACHE version in sw.js with each release
3. Test on your server before deploying to production
4. Consider hosting version.json on a CDN or your main server

This system ensures users always have the latest features and bug fixes while maintaining the offline-first PWA functionality!
